////local setups////
> install mongodb
> https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community
> download and install

#window
> in c drive make folder by the name of > data
> in data folder make folder by the name of > db

> open one cmd 
> go inside bin folder (c/programmeFile/mongodb/server/4.4/bin)
> mongod (this will start mongodb server on port 27017)

> open second cmd
> go inside bin folder 
> mongo (this will start mongodb console)

#mac/linux
> open terminal (~)
> mkdir data
> cd data
> mkdir db

> open terminal
> mongod --dbpath data/db (this will start mongodb server on port 27017)

> open terminal
> mongo (this will start mongodb console)

